comment.body:
@xvzcf I'm confused: Wasn't the statement yesterday that all sig-combinations can remain in as nothing breaks this way? The logic described above in my eyes is far from ideal: Do we really want to _remove completely_ from the standard build "interesting" signature combinations ("strong" PQ algorithm with "equivalent" classic algorithm)? 
And reading further into the changes: Do I read correctly in the PR that even plain, non-hybrid PQ sig algs get removed with this PR from the list of 'normally available' signature algorithms? I don't particularly like this. At the very least, I'd like to retain Dilithium3 over Dilithium2 (which security-wise is not really suitable anyway). But then again, strong Falcon also got removed -- and not just the hybrid... 
In general, my question is: What's the deciding factor as to which algorithms to keep by default enabled? If it's performance (?) I'm really unhappy with the default list in this PR. @christianpaquin @dstebila : What's your take on this?
